OL,3,CLack of leadership and support
OL,4,Ccriticised in review of SEND provision
OL,6,FOne of the problems highlighted is a
OL,7,Flack of "coherent and coordinated"
OL,8,Fthinking behind how to help special
OL,9,Fand mainstream schools deliver
OL,10,Fappropriate support, including
OL,11,Foffering sufficient training for
OL,12,Fschool staff.
OL,14,FThe review adds: "Typically, schools
OL,15,Ffeel they receive minimal support from
OL,16,FCYPES for SEND, often relying on their
OL,17,Fown initiatives, commissioning private
OL,18,Feducational psychologists (EPs), or
OL,19,Fcharity support.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/9
