OL,3,CLack of leadership and support
OL,4,Ccriticised in review of SEND provision
OL,6,FSchools say they feel "isolated and/or
OL,7,Funinvolved" in decisions made about
OL,8,FSEND provision, with the report
OL,9,Fstating that CYPES' central leadership
OL,10,Flacks commitment to "a common vision"
OL,11,Fand "a sense of shared responsibility".
OL,13,FOf those surveyed, 80% of schools said
OL,14,Fthey did not understand or know about
OL,15,FSEND decisions made centrally.
OL,17,FThe report also labels some key SEND
OL,18,Fpolicies as "out of date", although it
OL,19,Fdoes not specify which ones.
