OL,3,CLack of leadership and support
OL,4,Ccriticised in review of SEND provision
OL,6,FAnother barrier to better progress for
OL,7,Fpupils with SEND is said to be the
OL,8,FGovernment's varying spending
OL,9,Fcommitments for capital projects.
OL,11,FThe report states that changes in
OL,12,Ffunding and the pausing of
OL,13,Finfrastructure projects leave schools
OL,14,Ffeeling let down, with "insufficient
OL,15,Ftransparency" over the island's
OL,16,Feducation and inclusion budget.
OL,18,FDespite these challenges, many schools
OL,19,Fcontinue to be praised by parents for
OL,20,Fthe support they offer to SEND pupils.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/9
