OL,3,CLack of leadership and support
OL,4,Ccriticised in review of SEND provision
OL,6,FHowever, some families still feel like
OL,7,Ftheir opinions and requests are
OL,8,Fdisregarded when it comes to what
OL,9,Fprovision is appropriate for their
OL,10,Fchild and that schools are failing to
OL,11,Fadapt teaching methods, instead seeing
OL,12,Fchildren moved from mainstream
OL,13,Fsettings "if they don't fit in".
OL,15,FParents also highlight a lack of local
OL,16,FSEND expertise outside education, with
OL,17,Fsome saying the island has a "huge
OL,18,Fdearth" of specialists who can help
OL,19,Ftheir children take part in activities
OL,20,For join inclusive clubs.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G7/9
