OL,3,CLack of leadership and support
OL,4,Ccriticised in review of SEND provision
OL,6,FIn response, the Government of Jersey
OL,7,Fsays it "fully accepts the findings
OL,8,Fand has already begun implementing
OL,9,Fseveral recommendations", with recent
OL,10,Fchanges made in inclusion leadership -
OL,11,Fseconding experienced headteachers to
OL,12,Fbuild up the relationship between
OL,13,FCYPES and schools.
OL,15,FEducation Minister, Deputy Rob Ward,
OL,16,Fadds: "This review is a turning point.
OL,17,FIt gives us a clear roadmap for
OL,18,Fimprovement while recognising the
OL,19,Fstrengths and dedication of our
OL,20,Fschools.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G8/9
